               According to Zacks, "Sussex Bancorp is the holding company for the Sussex Bank, which operates through its main office in Franklin, New Jersey and branch offices in Andover, Augusta, Newton, Montague, Sparta, Vernon and Wantage, New Jersey and for Tri-State Insurance Agency, Inc, a full service insurance agency located in Augusta, New Jersey. Sussex Bancorp (NASDAQ:SBBX) traded up 1.99% on Wednesday, hitting $13.85. 16,074 shares of the company were exchanged. The firm has a 50 day moving average of $13.46 and a 200-day moving average of $13.09. The stock has a market cap of $63.54 million and a PE ratio of 14.73. Sussex Bancorp has a 52-week low of $11.43 and a 52-week high of $14.00. This story is the sole property of American Banking News and it was originally published by American Banking News. If you are reading this story on another website, that means this article was illegally copied and re-published to this website in violation of U.S. and International copyright law.
