ic CountiesHelping people across northern NJ with domestic disputes, work injuries, estate planning, and financial and business mattersWhen choosing a law firm to handle your important legal matters, experience, character, and empathy matter. New Jersey law firms come and go, but the firm of Hollander, Strelzik, Pasculli, Hinkes, Wojcik, Gacquin, Vandenberg & Hontz, L.L.C. has withstood the test of time. We have been serving your neighbors in Sussex, Warren, Morris and Passaic Counties for half a century. Through the years, we have been an integral part of the community, providing sound and trusted legal advice. We plan to continue that tradition of personal service and commitment for years to come.A history of providing excellent legal representationSince 1964, Hollander, Strelzik, Pasculli, Hinkes, Wojcik, Gacquin, Vandenberg & Hontz, L.L.C. has stood on the Square in Newton, serving people and businesses throughout northern New Jersey. Our clients consistently recognize the quality of our work and our genuine commitment to their interests. Many of our business law clients have maintained a relationship with our firm for years, even decades. Moreover, clients we have represented in elder law, workers’ compensation and family law matters frequently refer their friends and family members to us. We think that this is the highest compliment a law firm can receive, and we are committed to doing everything we can to continue to justify the confidence our clients have in us.Serving all of northern New JerseyLocated in Newton, our firm serves clients throughout northern New Jersey:MorrisBergenHunterdonEssexWarrenSomersetPassaicMiddlesexSussexOur attorneys work together, combining our unique insights, experiences and skills to provide all our clients with thorough legal advice and well-rounded representation.Providing the legal services you needAs a civil practice law firm that also provides services to those accused of criminal and municipal court offenses, including driving under the influence (DUI)/driving while intoxicated (DWI) and traffic violations, our goal is to offer the types of legal services people like you need most. We can assist you with any aspect of family law, including divorce, child custody and adoption. Attorney Catherine Anne Gaquin is a certified mediator, who provides mediation services to our family law clients. We can also help seniors and their families with various aspects of elder law, including estate planning, Medicare issues and Medicaid asset protection. Our lawyers work closely with you to give you the insight you need to make important life decisions with confidence.Through our business law practice, we have represented businesses of all types throughout New Jersey during all phases of their formation and development. In addition, our attorneys also represent individuals and businesses during bankruptcy proceedings. We have helped business people and entrepreneurs turn their ideas into functioning businesses. We manage legal issues throughout the lives of our clients’ companies and effectively use bankruptcy to provide them with a second chance when they run into trouble with business or personal finances.Contact a local Sussex County full-service law firm with roots in the community to discuss your caseIf you are a New Jersey resident in need of legal advice regarding workers’ compensation, family law, elder law, business law, or criminal law, or a DUI issue, call Hollander, Strelzik, Pasculli, Hinkes, Wojcik, Gacquin, Vandenberg & Hontz, L.L.C. today at 862-273-3465 or contact us online to schedule a meeting with one of our attorneys. We offer free initial consultations for family law and bankruptcy matters, and contingency fee arrangements for workers’ compensation, personal injury and disability cases. We offer competitive hourly rates for all other matters.      Meet Our Attorneys   Sanford Lloyd HollanderAlan StrelzikJanice D. PasculliWilliam E. HinkesMichael L. WojcikCatherine Anne GacquinJo